    {
      "Case Number": "CGC00313438",
      "Case Title": "ANDREWS VS NICHOLAS BACHKO COMPANY",
      "Court Date": "2002-04-12 09:30 AM",
      "Calendar Matter": "MOTION FOR SUMMARY JUDGMENT",
      "Rulings": "DENY MOTION FOR SUMMARY ADJUDICATION-- (1)ASSUMING THAT REG. 42.15-75(d) IS APPLICABLE, THERE IS A TRIABLE ISSUE OF FACT WHETHER THERE WERE SATISFACTORY MEANS TO ACCESS THE CRANE. (2)REG. 92.25-5 IS NOT APPLICABLE B/C THE PLATFORM WAS NOT A \"DECK.\" THE U.S. COAST GUARD DEFINES \"DECK\" AS A \"PERMANENT COVERING\" AND IT IS UNDISPUTED THAT THE CRANE WAS MOBILE. AT THE VERY LEAST, THERE IS A TRIABLE ISSUE OF FACT WHETHER THE PLATFORM WAS A \"DECK\" BASED UPON THE VARIOUS DEFINITIONS OF \"DECK.\" EVEN IF THE COURT ASSUMES THAT THE PLATFORM WAS A \"DECK,\" THERE IS A TRIABLE ISSUE OF FACT WHETHER THE DECK WAS \"GENERALLY ACCESSIBLE.\" (3)COURT REJECTS \"FOLLOWING ORDERS\" EXCEPTION TO COMPARATIVE NEGLIGENCE BECAUSE ORDERS NOT SPECIFIC OR URGENT. See Sineonoff v. Hiner, 249 F.3d 883, 891, fn.4 (9th Cir. 2001). (PB)"
    },
